{
  "title": "HASEN â€” Official Rules",
  "subtitle": "A trick-taking and betting game with fixed trumps and asymmetric interactions",
  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "components",
      "title": "1. Game Components",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "1.1 Hasen Deck (33 cards)",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The deck consists of 33 cards divided into 4 suits:"
            },
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "level": 4,
              "text": "Fixed Trump Suit: Flowers (8 cards)"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Ace (A) â€” 12 points",
                "King (K) â€” 11 points",
                "Queen (Q) â€” Karnoffel â€” 0 points (special trump)",
                "5 â€” 5 points",
                "4 â€” 4 points",
                "3 â€” 3 points",
                "2 â€” 2 points",
                "1 â€” 1 point"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "level": 4,
              "text": "Other Suits (Leaves, Berries, Acorns â€” 8 cards each)"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "10 â€” 10 points",
                "9 â€” 0 points",
                "8 â€” 0 points",
                "7 â€” 0 points",
                "6 â€” 0 points",
                "5 â€” 0 points",
                "Ober (O) â€” 4 points",
                "Unter (U) â€” 3 points"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "level": 4,
              "text": "Special S Cards (1 in each non-trump suit)"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Berries S â€” \"The Scythe\" â€” 0 points",
                "Leaves S â€” \"The Collector\" â€” 0 points",
                "Acorns S â€” \"The Leader's Choice\" â€” 0 points"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "1.2 Bid Cards",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "There are 3 types of bids available during each round:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "7 Points Bids â€” Predict your point total at round end",
                "6 Set Collection Bids â€” Collect specific suits while avoiding others",
                "5 Trick Bids â€” Win specific tricks or trick counts"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "During each round, 9 bids are randomly selected (3 of each type) and made available to players."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "1.3 Other Components",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Rabbit Tokens: 3 per player",
                "Score tracker or app"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "round-setup",
      "title": "2. Round Setup",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "2.1 Bid Pool",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "At the start of each round, 9 bid cards are randomly selected from the bid decks:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "3 Points bids",
                "3 Set Collection bids",
                "3 Trick bids"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "These bids are available for players to claim during the betting windows."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "2.2 Initial Deal",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Each player receives 5 cards:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "1 visible card (face-up, visible to all players, cannot be exchanged, joins hand after replacement phase)",
                "4 hidden cards (face-down in your hand)"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "2.3 Card Replacement Phase (Optional)",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "In turn order, each player may:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "ordered": true,
              "items": [
                "Discard 1 hidden card from their hand, reveal it to all players, and draw a new card from the deck or from the discard pile",
                "Skip replacement and immediately gain +3 points"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Discarded cards remain visible. Later players may take a discarded card instead of drawing from the deck."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "round-play",
      "title": "3. Round Play (Tricks)",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "A round consists of 6 tricks. In each trick, all players play 1 card."
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "3.1 Leadership Rule",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "The player who opens the 1st trick of the game is the player who most recently saw a rabbit",
                "In subsequent rounds, the lead player rotates clockwise",
                "The winner of each trick leads the next trick, unless someone played Acorns S (Leader's Choice)"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "3.2 Leading the Suit",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The first card played in a trick establishes the led suit. This becomes the most powerful suit for that trick (except for trumps)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "3.3 No Suit Following Required",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Players may play any card regardless of the led suit."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "3.4 Trick Resolution",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The trick is won by the strongest card according to the Card Hierarchy (section 4)."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "card-hierarchy",
      "title": "4. Complete Card Hierarchy",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Cards are divided into 4 power levels, plus 3 special S cards with unique rules."
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "Level 1 â€” Major Trumps (strongest in the game)",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "These cards always win except against The Scythe when it leads."
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Ace of Flowers â€” 12 pts",
                "King of Flowers â€” 11 pts",
                "Queen of Flowers (Karnoffel) â€” 0 pts"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Special Karnoffel Rule: The only card capable of beating The Scythe when The Scythe leads the trick."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "Level 2 â€” Major Colors (only when led suit matches)",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "These cards are only strong when the led suit matches their suit."
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Obers of Leaves / Berries / Acorns â€” 4 pts",
                "Unters of Leaves / Berries / Acorns â€” 3 pts"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Beat: all minor trumps. Lose to: major trumps."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "Level 3 â€” Minor Trumps (common Flowers)",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Function as trumps but don't beat Obers/Unters of the led suit."
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "5 of Flowers â€” 5 pts",
                "4 of Flowers â€” 4 pts",
                "3 of Flowers â€” 3 pts",
                "2 of Flowers â€” 2 pts",
                "1 of Flowers â€” 1 pt"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Beat: any card from another suit that isn't a Major Color. Lose to: Major Colors of the led suit."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "Level 4 â€” Minor Colors",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Only participate if their suit is led."
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "10, 9, 8, 7, 6, 5 of the led suit"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Rule: If the suit is not led â†’ always lose to any trump."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "special-cards",
      "title": "5. Special S Cards",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "ðŸ”´ Berries S â€” \"The Scythe\"",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Cannot open the 1st trick of the round",
                "If it leads â†’ wins against everything except Karnoffel (Flowers Q)",
                "If it doesn't lead â†’ functions as a Minor Color"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Typical use: Finish a round or force a guaranteed win by leading."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "ðŸ”µ Acorns S â€” \"The Leader's Choice\"",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Cannot win the trick",
                "When played, its owner chooses who leads the next trick, completely ignoring the current winner"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Typical use: Tactical control of play order."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "ðŸŸ¤ Leaves S â€” \"The Collector\"",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Cannot win the trick",
                "At the end of the trick where it was played, the player takes one card from the trick and places it in their personal score reserve"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Typical use: Acquire Aces, Kings, or major trumps without winning them by strength."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "betting-phase",
      "title": "6. Betting Phase",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "There are 3 betting windows during the round:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "ordered": true,
          "items": [
            "From the start until the end of the 1st trick",
            "From playing the 1st card of the 2nd trick until its end",
            "From playing the 1st card of the 3rd trick until its end"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "6.1 Betting Rules",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Each player can make one bet per window (max 3 bids per round)",
                "Place a rabbit token on the chosen bid card",
                "You can bet before or after playing your card in the trick",
                "Bets are public",
                "You can combine bids only if they are of different categories",
                "Maximum 2 players per specific bid"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "6.2 Penalty for Failed Bids",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Set Collection bids:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Window 1 â†’ -10 pts",
                "Window 2 â†’ -15 pts",
                "Window 3 â†’ -20 pts"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Points and Trick bids:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Window 1 â†’ -20 pts",
                "Window 2 â†’ -25 pts",
                "Window 3 â†’ -30 pts"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "6.3 Bid Conflicts",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "If two or more players choose the same bid in the same window:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "If all win or all lose â†’ no additional effect",
                "If some win and others lose:",
                "  â€¢ Winners: +5 pts",
                "  â€¢ Losers: -5 pts (in addition to normal penalty)"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "bid-types",
      "title": "7. Bid Types",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "7.1 Points Bids",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Objective: Predict how many card points you'll accumulate by round end."
            },
            {
              "type": "table",
              "headers": ["Bid Name", "Condition", "Success Reward"],
              "rows": [
                ["Smallest", "Score 2-10 pts", "+40 pts"],
                ["Tiny", "Score 3-15 pts", "+40 pts"],
                ["Small", "Score 5-20 pts", "+30 pts"],
                ["Normal", "Score 11-30 pts", "+40 pts"],
                ["Medium", "Score 22-40 pts", "+35 pts"],
                ["Large", "Score 35+ pts", "+45 pts"],
                ["Largest", "Score 45+ pts", "+55 pts"]
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "7.2 Set Collection Bids",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Objective: Collect cards of certain suits and avoid others. All cards won in tricks plus those acquired by effects (like The Collector) are evaluated."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Available combinations:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Collect Acorns / Avoid Leaves",
                "Collect Acorns / Avoid Berries",
                "Collect Berries / Avoid Acorns",
                "Collect Berries / Avoid Leaves",
                "Collect Leaves / Avoid Berries",
                "Collect Leaves / Avoid Acorns"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "heading",
              "level": 4,
              "text": "How Set Collection Bids are Scored"
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Success: You receive +10 points per collected card of the target suit."
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Failure: You receive a penalty for each forbidden card you obtained:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Window 1: -10 per forbidden card",
                "Window 2: -15 per forbidden card",
                "Window 3: -20 per forbidden card"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Net calculation: (collected cards Ã— 10) - (forbidden cards Ã— penalty). You win the bid if the net is â‰¥ 10 points."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "7.3 Trick Bids",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Objective: Win specific tricks or trick counts."
            },
            {
              "type": "table",
              "headers": ["Bid Name", "Condition", "Success Reward", "Notes"],
              "rows": [
                ["Final Double", "Win the last 2 tricks", "+30 pts", "2 available"],
                ["Only Final Double", "Win exactly the last 2 tricks and no others", "+40 pts", "2 available"],
                ["Four Tricks", "Win 4 tricks", "+45 pts", ""],
                ["Single Trick", "Win exactly 1 trick", "+45 pts", ""],
                ["Perfect", "Win all 6 tricks", "+55 pts", ""]
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "round-end",
      "title": "8. Round End and Game End",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "8.1 Round End",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "Points are totaled from:"
            },
            {
              "type": "list",
              "items": [
                "Cards won (if no bids were made)",
                "Successful bids",
                "Failed bids (penalties)",
                "Special card effects",
                "Card replacement bonus (+3 if skipped)"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection",
          "title": "8.2 Game End",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "text": "The game ends when a player reaches the agreed-upon target score (e.g., 200 or 300 points). The player with the highest total score wins."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
